<name>SUSPENSION &amp; AXLE</name>
<section id="1000J_S000L" variety="S000L">
<name>TIRE AND WHEEL</name>
<ttl id="1000J_S000L_7A80C_T004Q" variety="T004Q">
<name>TIRE AND WHEEL SYSTEM</name>
<para id="RM0000010MW00TX" category="G" type-id="3001K" name-id="TW1MB-01" from="201202" to="201403">
<name>INSPECTION</name>
<subpara id="RM0000010MW00TX_01" type-id="01" category="01">
<s-1 id="RM0000010MW00TX_01_0001" proc-id="RM21Q0EV__00001KS00000">
<ptxt>INSPECT TIRE</ptxt>
<content1 releasenbr="1">
<s2>
<ptxt>Measure the tires for wear and proper inflation pressure.</ptxt>
<spec>
<title>Standard cold tire inflation pressure</title>
<table>
<tgroup cols="3">
<colspec colname="COL1" colwidth="1.38in"/>
<colspec colname="COL2" colwidth="1.38in"/>
<colspec colname="COL3" colwidth="1.37in"/>
<thead>
<row>
<entry>
<ptxt>Tire Size</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry>
<ptxt>Front Pressure</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry>
<ptxt>Rear Pressure</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</thead>
<tbody>
<row>
<entry>
<ptxt>195/70R 14 91S</ptxt>
<ptxt>205/65R 15 94S</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry>
<ptxt>230 kPa (2.3 kgf/cm<sup>2</sup>, 33 psi)</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry>
<ptxt>230 kPa (2.3 kgf/cm<sup>2</sup>, 33 psi)</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</spec>
</s2>
<s2>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname="R003031E02" width="2.775699831in" height="1.771723296in"/>
</figure>
<ptxt>Using a dial indicator, measure the tire runout.</ptxt>
<spec>
<title>Standard tire runout</title>
<specitem>
<ptxt>3.0 mm (0.118 in.) or less</ptxt>
</specitem>
</spec>
</s2>
</content1>
</s-1>
<s-1 id="RM0000010MW00TX_01_0002" proc-id="RM21Q0EV__00001KT00000">
<ptxt>ROTATE TIRE</ptxt>
<content1 releasenbr="1">
<s2>
<ptxt>Rotate the tires.</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname="C113172E01" width="2.775699831in" height="3.779676365in"/>
</figure>
<atten4>
<ptxt>The rotation method is different depending on the type of the vehicle's wheels and spare tire's wheel (see illustration).</ptxt>
</atten4>
</s2>
</content1>
</s-1>
<s-1 id="RM0000010MW00TX_01_0005" proc-id="RM21Q0EV__00001KW00000">
<ptxt>INSPECT WHEEL BALANCE</ptxt>
<content1 releasenbr="1">
<figure>
<graphic graphicname="C080976E02" width="2.775699831in" height="1.771723296in"/>
</figure>
<s2>
<ptxt>Check and adjust the balance of the wheels.</ptxt>
<spec>
<title>Standard imbalance after adjustment</title>
<table>
<tgroup cols="2">
<colspec colname="COL1" colwidth="2.07in"/>
<colspec colname="COL2" colwidth="2.06in"/>
<thead>
<row>
<entry>
<ptxt>Tire Size</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry>
<ptxt>Balance Weight</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</thead>
<tbody>
<row>
<entry>
<ptxt>195/70R 14 91S</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry>
<ptxt>15 g (0.033 lb) or less</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry>
<ptxt>205/65R 15 94S</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry>
<ptxt>14 g (0.030 lb) or less</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</spec>
</s2>
</content1>
</s-1>
<s-1 id="RM0000010MW00TX_01_0003" proc-id="RM21Q0EV__00001KU00000">
<ptxt>INSPECT WHEEL BEARING BACKLASH</ptxt>
<content1 releasenbr="1">
<s2>
<ptxt>Inspect the front wheel bearing backlash (see page <xref label="Seep01" href="RM000000ZZM00IX_01_0001"/>).</ptxt>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>Inspect the rear wheel bearing backlash (see page <xref label="Seep02" href="RM000000ZZW00IX_01_0001"/>).</ptxt>
</s2>
</content1>
</s-1>
<s-1 id="RM0000010MW00TX_01_0004" proc-id="RM21Q0EV__00001KV00000">
<ptxt>INSPECT FOR AXLE HUB DEVIATION</ptxt>
<content1 releasenbr="1">
<s2>
<ptxt>Inspect for front axle hub deviation (see page <xref label="Seep01" href="RM000000ZZM00IX_01_0001"/>).</ptxt>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>Inspect for rear axle hub deviation (see page <xref label="Seep02" href="RM000000ZZW00IX_01_0001"/>).</ptxt>
</s2>
</content1>
</s-1>
</subpara>
</para>
